On Mon, Jul 25, 2016 at 3:00 PM, Students' General Secretary, IIT Madras <
gen_sec@smail.iitm.ac.in> wrote:

> *Institute Web and Mobile Operations Team 2016-17*
>
> Hello all,
>
> Here is the call for coordinators for Institute WebOps/MobOps team.
>
> Anyone who has interest in web hosting, designing websites, building
> chrome extensions or hybrid mobile and desktop applications may apply for
> the post. This is open only for B.Tech/Dual Degree *second years*. The
> selection will be based on an interview during which an assignment will be
> given. Based on which, one might get selected into the team.
>
> *Who are we?*
>
> In the past the institute Web Operations team has been taking care of
> entire student related web operations such as students portal, mess registration
> and has assisted Hostels, CFI, IBOT, techsoc, Sports, NSS, EML etc. in setting
> up and running their websites. We have brought about many new initiatives
> this year, which will further our cause to ease student life in insti and
> also help organize information over time. Some of our many new initiatives
> include IITM Video Conference app <http://students.iitm.ac.in/iitm_video>
> , Information Portal <http://students.iitm.ac.in/iportal>, Insti Maps
> <http://students.iitm.ac.in/maps> , Course Review
> <https://students.iitm.ac.in/reviewCourses/> , Research Portal
> <https://students.iitm.ac.in/research/login> and many other backend
> features to bring about a centralization among the sites. We have been
> developed a mobile app for integrated use of all these sites, as well as
> browser extensions to make them more accessible. You can find it here
> <https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=in.ac.iitm.students&hl=en>
>  .
> The coming year a number of projects like " Notifications portal,
> Students Library , HAS Portal , Buy and Sell " etc. are being brought. We
> are mainly looking forward to standardize and build upon the existing
> sites, hoping that they be more useful for each students in our institute.
> There is definitely a lot of exciting work waiting to be done!
>
>
> *Eligibility Criterion:*
>
>    - Minimum CGPA of 7 with no "U" or "W" or "I" in the grade card as on
>    today.
>    - Successful completion of NCC/NSO/NSS.
>    - No history of punishment by the academic and the hostel disciplinary
>    committee.
>
> *Incentives Offered:*
>
>    - Chance to implement your own ideas in the institute and to get them certified
>    as an internship.
>    - T-shirts and Treats.
>    - Recommendation to Web based start ups and core/coordinator positions
>    of other web operations team operating in the Institute.
>
> *Deadline for the application of the post is 11:59pm, 07-08-2016.*
>
> Please fill the form to apply for the post:
> *Institute WebOps/MobOps - Call for Coordinators
> <https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1s_-W1dNJa57GvgjFK3g7Y6Geul0txAIcy5TTBntvWhI>*
>
> The details of the interview will be mailed to the candidates on
> *09-08-2016*.
>
> *P.S :*  We also have two positions open for super coordinator open for
> 3rd years and above . If interested fill this form
> <https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdk6sEMgfWJhYlOIVBrLiubjvEHJ_Lq-rIgQZlMTgh65B0gkQ/viewform>
>  before *11:59pm, 07-08-2016*.
